    passage: "A publisher noticed that its novels with brightly colored covers sell more copies than its novels with muted covers. Concluding that bright covers cause higher sales, the publisher decided to reissue its entire backlist with brightly colored covers, expecting each reissued title to sell more copies as a result.",
