    id: "gmat_0042", topicId: 1, domain: "Verbal Reasoning", skill: "Reading Comprehension", difficulty: 2,
    passage: "A recent report on remote work concluded that employees who work from home are more productive than their office-based counterparts, pointing to survey data in which remote workers reported completing more tasks per week. The report's author acknowledged, however, that the surveyed remote workers were disproportionately drawn from software and writing professions, whose output is comparatively easy to quantify in discrete tasks. Office-based workers in the sample, by contrast, more often held roles centered on meetings and coordination. The author nonetheless treated the task-completion figures as directly comparable across the two groups.",
    question: "Which of the following, if true, would most strengthen a challenge to the report's conclusion?",
